// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// SUPABASE ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION TEMPLATE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 
// ⚠️  IMPORTANT: This file contains sensitive credentials
// ⚠️  NEVER commit this to public repositories with real values
// ⚠️  If values are exposed, regenerate your Anon Key in Supabase dashboard
//
// INSTRUCTIONS:
// 1. Copy this file as ".env.local" (in your project root)
// 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Supabase credentials
// 3. This file is listed in .gitignore (should not be committed)
// 4. For production, use proper environment variable management
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// Your Supabase Project URL
// Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project URL
// Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

// Your Supabase Anon Key (Public, safe for client-side)
// Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API Keys > Anon Key
// Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

// Optional: Service Role Key (DO NOT use in browser code)
// Only for backend/server-side code
// Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API Keys > Service Role
# VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// USAGE IN YOUR CODE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// For development (with bundler like Vite):
// const url = import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_URL;
// const key = import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY;
//
// For simple HTML pages (like this project):
// - Use supabase-config.js instead
// - Update it directly with your credentials
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
